Methods in Java;
methods/Functions/Behaviours are blocks of code.They contain statements (lines of codes)
which are executed when a method is called.

A method in Java  has return type(outputs), name and parameters/arguments.


Why should we use methods?
 Methods heps us reuse the code. when we need to share or reuse a piece of code within our
 projects or with others
 we can create our own classes define methods inside those classes and we can start reusing/sharing them.

Syntax of the method;
Return Type (output)   nameOfTheMethod (input/argument/parameter ( OPTIONAL ) ){


}
All the methods needs to be created inside a class.



